sequenceDiagram
    participant Build as Konflux Build Pipeline
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>registry.redhat.io / quay.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as rhods-operator<br/>Platform Operator
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>Envoy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Workbench Container<br/>JupyterLab / code-server / RStudio<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant External as External Services<br/>PyPI / Git / S3 / MongoDB

    Note over Build,Registry: Flow 1: Workbench Image Deployment

    Build->>Registry: Push container images<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Service Account
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply kustomize manifests<br/>(create ImageStreams)<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStream annotations<br/>(opendatahub.io/notebook-image-name, etc.)<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: User Notebook Session

    User->>Dashboard: Select workbench image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: OAuth/OIDC SSO
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note right of K8sAPI: ODH Notebook Controller<br/>creates StatefulSet +<br/>kube-rbac-proxy sidecar

    K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull workbench image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: Pull Secret

    User->>Gateway: Access notebook UI<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: OAuth/OIDC cookie
    Gateway->>RBAC: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer token
    RBAC->>Notebook: Proxy to workbench<br/>8888/TCP HTTP<br/>(localhost/pod network, pre-authenticated)
    Notebook-->>RBAC: Response
    RBAC-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Notebook UI

    Note over Notebook,External: Runtime Egress (User-Initiated)

    Notebook->>External: pip install (PyPI)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Notebook->>External: git clone (repos)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Notebook->>External: Data access (S3)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: AWS IAM / S3 creds
    Notebook->>External: Database query (MongoDB)<br/>27017/TCP<br/>Auth: Credentials
